{"parse":{"title":"Growth point","pageid":9304082,"revid":856378244,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-style\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e1/Ambox_wikify.svg/40px-Ambox_wikify.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e1/Ambox_wikify.svg/60px-Ambox_wikify.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e1/Ambox_wikify.svg/80px-Ambox_wikify.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"620\" data-file-height=\"620\" /></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>needs more <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style/Linking\" title=\"Wikipedia:Manual of Style/Linking\">links to other articles</a> to help <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:BUILD\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wikipedia:BUILD\">integrate it into the encyclopedia</a></b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please help <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Growth_point&amp;action=edit\">improve this article</a> by adding links <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Only_make_links_that_are_relevant_to_the_context\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wikipedia:Only make links that are relevant to the context\">that are relevant to the context</a> within the existing text.</span>  <small><i>(September 2015)</i></small><small class=\"hide-when-compact\"><i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal\" title=\"Help:Maintenance template removal\">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table><p>\nA <b>Growth Point</b> is a technical term in <a href=\"/wiki/Cognitive_linguistics\" title=\"Cognitive linguistics\">cognitive linguistics</a> and gesture research. It refers to the earliest beginnings of a spoken <a href=\"/wiki/Utterance\" title=\"Utterance\">utterance</a> in the mind of a speaker, combining the beginnings of a <a href=\"/wiki/Mimetic_theory_of_speech_origins\" title=\"Mimetic theory of speech origins\">mimetic gesture</a> with the preliminary verbal expression of the person's thought.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> </p><style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r856303468\">.mw-parser-output .templatequote{overflow:hidden;margin:1em 0;padding:0 40px}.mw-parser-output .templatequote .templatequotecite{line-height:1.5em;text-align:left;padding-left:1.6em;margin-top:0}</style><blockquote class=\"templatequote\"><p>The growth point is the speaker's minimal idea unit that can develop into a full utterance together with a gesture... the content of the growth point tends to be the novel departure of thought from the presupposed background. It is the element of thought that stands out in the context and may be the point of greatest relevance...  The concept of the growth point unites image, word and pragmatic content into a single unit.</p><div class=\"templatequotecite\">\u2014&#8201;<cite><cite class=\"citation\"><i><span></span></i>McNeill, D.1992. <i> Hand and Mind: What Gestures Reveal about Thought. </i>Chicago and London: The University of Chicago Press, p. 220.<i><span></span></i></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=McNeill%2C+D.1992.++Hand+and+Mind%3A+What+Gestures+Reveal+about+Thought.+Chicago+and+London%3A+The+University+of+Chicago+Press%2C+p.+220.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGrowth+point\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Growth_point&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">D. McNeill, S. Duncan, J. Cole et al. 2008. Growth Points from the Very Beginning. <i>Interaction Studies</i> <b>9</b>: 117-132.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">McNeill, D.1992. <i> Hand and Mind: What Gestures Reveal about Thought.. </i>Chicago and London: The University of Chicago Press</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2198\nCached time: 20180916022508\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.080 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.128 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 258/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 10400/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1629/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 2/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 1063/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.035/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 1.89 MB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  115.388      1 -total\n 49.55%   57.170      1 Template:Quotation\n 38.63%   44.579      1 Template:Underlinked\n 28.93%   33.379      1 Template:Citation\n 24.43%   28.193      1 Template:Ambox\n 10.33%   11.914      1 Template:Comma_separated_entries\n 10.01%   11.547      1 Template:Reflist\n  4.53%    5.230      3 Template:If_empty\n  2.03%    2.341      1 Template:Main_other\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:9304082-0!cano